text: Saint-Thégonnec () is a former commune. It is found in the region Brittany in the Finistère department in the northwest of France. On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune of Saint-Thégonnec Loc-Eguiner.Arrêté préfectoral 23 December 2015 == References == Category:Former communes in Finistère
title: Saint-Thégonnec
